A whole AppleTV Web Server Solution Stack Composition. Have a look at http://goo.gl/LXfUB .
 A whole AppleTV Web Server Solution Stack Composition.
 
 PLEASE DO NOT INSTALL THIS PACKAGES ON YOUR iPHONE, iPOD OR iPAD!
 YOUR BATTERY WILL BE EMPTY VERY SOON! INSTEAD USE THE CYDIA PACKAGE BELOW:
 'ios-lighttpd-php-mysql'
 You will get more information here: http://goo.gl/LXfUB
  
 If you are not familiar in operation of console and shell scripting please don't install this package!
 
 This cydia package will install some sub cydia packages like:
 
 PHP54 v5.4.8
 Lighttpd-atv v1.4.31
 MySQL-atv v5.1.66
 
 The localtion of your web files is /var/www
 If you need write permission to a www file or folder, change the owner to 'daemon:_www'
 The MySQL root user password is not set during the installation. Please change it as soon as possible. 

 You will find the MySQL database files at /var/mysql
 
 With this cydia package you are now free to host your own Content Management Systems (CMS), Blogs, Bulletin Boards or File Servers.
 Such as ownCloud, WebsiteBaker, Contao, TYPO3, WordPress, Joomla!, phpBB, miniBB, etc.
 
 Additional 'example' config files below are installed:
 
 /etc/php.ini
 /etc/lighttpd/lighttpd-atv.conf
 /etc/lighttpd/mod_fastcgi-atv.conf
 
 Furthermore some daemon launcher are installed:
 
 /Library/LaunchDaemons/com.atv.mysql.plist 
 /Library/LaunchDaemons/com.atv.lighttpd.plist
 
 Existing config files will be backed up.
 
 If it is possible, please symlink the folder /usr/local to /var/stash/local.
 Through that the packages data are not stored on your small first ATV flash partition.
 
 To set your MySQL database root password, please run the command below from a ssh console after the installation:
 /usr/local/bin/mysql_secure_installation
 
 If you would like to reinitialize your MySQL database please use this command:
 /usr/local/bin/mysql_install_db --user=daemon
 
 You can stop and kill the Lighttpd and MySQL daemons with the commds below:
 launchctl unload -w /Library/LaunchDaemons/com.atv.lighttpd.plist
 launchctl unload -w /Library/LaunchDaemons/com.atv.mysql.plist
 killall lighttpd
 killall mysqld
 
 If you would like to get more package information, please have a look at http://goo.gl/LXfUB .
 
